CATEGORY=Special Ability|CotSP ~ Weapons and Armor.MOD	DESC:Cultists of the Shattered Peak are proficient with all simple and martial weapons, as well as with light armor and bucklers.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|CotSP ~ Spells.MOD				DESC:Cultists of the Shattered Peak can cast a limited number of arcane spells. Cultist must have an Intelligence score of at 10 + the spell's level. Bonus spells are based on Intelligence and saving throws against these spells have a DC of 10 + spell level + INT modifier. Bonus spells are also based upon Intelligence. Cultists can learn Sorcerer/Wizard spells from the schools of Abjuration or Enchantment only. Spells are prepared and cast in the same was a Wizard.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|CotSP ~ Ominous Presence.MOD	DESC:Cultists gain a bonus equal to their class level on all Bluff and Intimidate checks.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|CotSP ~ Zeal.MOD				DESC:Cultists gain a +1 morale bonus on attack rolls against arcane casters and a +1 morale bonus against arcane spells and effects. These bonuses do not apply a creature with arcane spell-like abilities unless it is also an arcane caster.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|CotSP ~ Sneak Attack.MOD		DESC:Beginning at 2nd level, Cultists deal 1d6 extra damage when they flank an opponent or at any time when the target is denied its Dexterity bonus. This bonus damage increases to 2d6 at 4th level. This combines with the sneak attack of other classes.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|CotSP ~ Smite Mage.MOD			DESC:Beginning at 3rd level, a Cultist can attempt to smite an arcane spell caster with one normal melee attack once per day. Cultists add their CHA (%1) to their attack roll and deal 1 point of extra damage per class level (%2) on a successful attack. If the target is not an arcane spellcaster, the smite has no effect but the ability is still used up for the day.|CHA|CotSPLVL
CATEGORY=Special Ability|CotSP ~ Death Attack.MOD		DESC:At 5th level, a Cultist gains a death attack that works like the assassin ability of the same name, except the DC of the Fortitude check to avoid the death or paralysis is 15 + INT (%1)|(15+INT)


