CATEGORY=Special Ability|Olin Gisir ~ Ancient Knowledge.MOD		DESC:An Olin Gisir's study of ancient lore grants a +1 bonus on Knowledge (Arcana), Knowledge (History), and Use Magic Device checks. They also gain the same bonus on Bardic Knowledge checks if they possess that class feature. This bonus increases to +2 at 4th level, to +3 at 7th level, and finally to +4 at 10th level.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Olin Gisir ~ Secret.MOD				DESC:Olin Gisir's pickup countless bits of forgotten lore from ancient tomes, the whispers of imprisoned fiends, and other even more dangerous sources. At 1st, 4th, 7th, and 10th level the Olin Gisir can choose from an array of secrets determined by combining Intelligence modifier and class level (%1) to meet or exceed the value on the selection table.|OlinGisirSecretsLVL
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Olin Gisir ~ Signs.MOD					DESC:Beginning at 2nd level an Olin Gisir learns to ferret out ancient, hidden evils by reading mystic omens in the world around them. Three times per day the Olin Gisir can cast Augury (caster level equal to character level).
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Olin Gisir ~ Word of Dispel.MOD		DESC:At 5th level, an Olin Gisir gains additional power against old perils they seek to destroy or subdue. They can add either Dispel Chaos, Dispel Evil, or Dispel Law to the 5th level arcane spells that they can cast. Wizards can add the spell to their spellbook and Sorcerers receive it as a bonus known spell.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Olin Gisir ~ Word of Might.MOD			DESC:At 8th level, an Olin Gisir can use words of power against their enemies. They can add either Dictum, Holy Word, or Word of Chaos to the 7th level arcane spells that they can cast. Wizards can add the spell to their spellbook and Sorcerers receive it as a bonus known spell.

