CATEGORY=Special Ability|Sunmaster ~ Sun Spells.MOD				DESC:Sunmasters can prepare any Sun domain spell as if it were on their divine spell list.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Sunmaster ~ Glaring Eyes.MOD			DESC:Beginning at 2nd level, a Sunmaster's eyes glow with the brilliant orange color of the sun. They can produce a Searing Light effect from their eyes %1/day. Additionally, they can never be blinded or dazed by spells or effects with the Light descriptor or by natural light of any kind. A Sunmaster can use Searing Light twice per day at 5th level and three times per day at 8th level.|SunmasterGlaringEyesUsages
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Sunmaster ~ Resistance to Fire.MOD		DESC:Beginning 3rd level, a Sunmaster's link to the sun gives them increased resistance to fire. At 3rd level fire resistance is 5, increasing to 10 at 6th level, and finally to 15 at 9th level. 
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Sunmaster ~ Law Spells.MOD				DESC:Sunmasters can prepare any Law domain spell as if it were on their divine spell list.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Sunmaster ~ Planning Domain.MOD		DESC:At 7th level, a Sunmaster gains access to the Planning domain and acquires its granted ability.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Sunmaster ~ Sunform.MOD				DESC:Upon reaching 10th level, a Sunmaster gains the ability to become an insubstantial ball of bright, glowing light the size of a medium creature. This effect is identical to that of the Gaseous Form spell, except as follows: in Sunform the Sunmaster radiates Daylight (as spell), can fly at 120 feet (perfect), and has immunity to fire, light, and air effects. In addition, Sunmasters gain a melee touch attack that deals 6d6 point of fire damage. A Sunmaster can remain in Sunform for 10 rounds. Sunform is the equivalent of an 8th-level spell and is usable once per day.

